curam.util.ctm.bom.impl

Class CodeTableExistenceBOMImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.ctm.bom.BusinessObjectModuleImpl
      • curam.util.ctm.bom.impl.CodeTableExistenceBOMImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BusinessObjectModule, ExistenceBOM

    public class CodeTableExistenceBOMImpl
extends BusinessObjectModuleImpl
implements ExistenceBOM
    This is the Existence Business Object Module implementation for a Code Table BOM. A Code Table BOM consists of the Code Table Header record and its associated code table item records. This class determines if a Code Table BOM exists on the target system.

    • Constructor Summary

      CodeTableExistenceBOMImpl()
      This is a no-arg constructor setting the business object type to be Code Table and the offset to 0.

      • isBusinessObjectExist

        public boolean isBusinessObjectExist(BusinessObjectIdentifier businessObjectIdentifier,
                                     org.w3c.dom.Document boDocument)
                              throws AppException,
                                     InformationalException
        This determines if a Code Table BOM exists on the database. The businessObjectIdentifier will contain the code table name which is the unique identifier for a Code Table BOM. This method will return true if the specified Code Table BOM exists in the target system, false otherwise.
        Specified by:
        isBusinessObjectExist in interface ExistenceBOM
        Parameters:
        businessObjectIdentifier - Contains the code table name.
        boDocument - Contains XML document representation of business object content.
        Returns:
        True if the Code Table BOM exists, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        AppException - Generic exception signature.
        InformationalException - Generic exception signature.
